# Acces spre Succes — Project Context

Website for Asociația "Acces spre Succes" (NGO from Bistrița, Romania).
Three independently deployable services in one git repo:

- `backend/` — Spring Boot REST API
- `client-frontend/` — public site
- `admin-frontend/` — admin panel

Local dev runs everything via `docker-compose.yml` at the repo root.

## Stack

### Backend (`backend/`)
- Java 21, Spring Boot 4.0.0-M3 (milestone), Maven
- Spring Web + Spring Data JPA + Hibernate (`ddl-auto=update`)
- Spring Security 7 + JJWT 0.12.6 for JWT auth (HS256, 24h)
- BCrypt for password hashes
- PostgreSQL via JDBC (`postgresql` driver)
- Uploads stored on local FS at `${file.upload-dir:uploads}` — needs a persistent volume in production
- `stripe-java` is being phased out for EuPlătesc

### Database
- Neon Postgres (cloud) — connection string via `DB_URL` / `DB_USER` / `DB_PASSWORD`
- Plain PostgreSQL, swappable with Supabase or any Postgres just by changing the env vars

### Frontends — both share the same shape
- React 19 + Vite 5, vanilla JS/JSX (no TypeScript)
- Build output goes to `build/` (legacy CRA convention, not Vite's default `dist/`)
- API URL comes from `src/config.js`, which reads `VITE_API_BASE_URL` at build time
- Vite dev server → `http://localhost:8080`
- Vercel build → `https://api.acces-spre-succes.ro`
- Docker / nginx → relative `/api` (proxied by frontend container)
- `client-frontend/`: axios, framer-motion, react-i18next, react-router-dom 7, @stripe/stripe-js
- `admin-frontend/`: lean — only react/react-dom; uses `fetch` via `authFetch`

## Auth

- JWT in `Authorization: Bearer ...`, persisted in `localStorage`
- Initial admin seeded on first boot from `ADMIN_BOOTSTRAP_USERNAME` / `ADMIN_BOOTSTRAP_PASSWORD`
- `admin-frontend/src/services/auth.js` exports `authFetch` — every admin API call must go through it so the token is auto-attached
- `backend/src/main/java/com/test/site_ong/auth/` holds all the security wiring

## Deployment

- Public site → **Vercel**, Root Directory `client-frontend`, domain `acces-spre-succes.ro`
- Admin panel → **Vercel**, Root Directory `admin-frontend`, domain `admin.acces-spre-succes.ro`
- Backend → **Fly.io**, region `fra` (Frankfurt), domain `api.acces-spre-succes.ro`
- DNS → **Cloudflare**, all records DNS-only (gray cloud); Vercel and Fly.io handle their own TLS
- Each Vercel project must set `VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.acces-spre-succes.ro`

## Conventions

- Secrets live in `.env` (gitignored); `.env.example` is the committed template
- Never hardcode URLs or DB creds — read from `config.js` (frontends) or `application.properties` placeholders (backend)
- Prefer Vite/Spring built-in env-var resolution over runtime config files
- Spring Security rules live in `backend/src/main/java/com/test/site_ong/auth/config/SecurityConfig.java`
- Frontends were migrated CRA → Vite; do not reintroduce `react-scripts`
- Lockfiles (`package-lock.json`) are committed — keep them in sync with `package.json`

## Common gotchas

- Vercel needs the **Root Directory** saved separately from the Build Settings panel
- Fly.io machine filesystems are ephemeral — uploaded images need a mounted volume (`/app/uploads`)
- Spring Boot `ddl-auto=update` means schema changes from entity edits land automatically; treat entity changes as migrations
